<div id='content'>
<div align='center'><b><span style='font-weight: bold;'>Hello, feel free to look around, but you'll need to earn some more civics points before you can make a purchase.</span><br><br>
</b></div>
Welcome to the Donation Center! If you'd like to contribute a used or unwanted object, then our Director of Donations, Mr. Laslo Balint, will be more than happy to accept your contribution. The Donation Center accepts books, clothes, furniture and toys. Unfortunately food, pets, and pet notes cannot be accepted.<br><h3 align='center'>How to make a donation:</h3>As you look through Your Stuff, you'll notice a <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/icon_donate_2_v1.gif'> icon on the right (next to the Yard Sale, Basement, and Throw Out! icons). When you select the <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/icon_donate_2_v1.gif'> icon, you'll be asked to certify that you want to contribute this object to the Community Center's donation program. If you click "Yes" and go forward with your donation, then you'll receive a message stating that your contribution has been received. If you'd like to make a donation now, go to <a href='/inventory.phtml'>your stuff</a> and click the donate icon next to the item.<br><br>Those who participate in the donation program receive civic recognition for their generosity. Citizens with strong civics scores will be given the chance, once per day, to make a purchase from the Donation Center.
